This is a Python project building an agentic RAG system for sports medicine research.

Stack: Python 3.11+, FastAPI, Qdrant (vector DB), Anthropic Claude API, LangGraph.

Structure:
- src/ingestion/ — PubMed fetching, chunking, metadata extraction
- src/retrieval/ — Qdrant storage, search, re-ranking
- src/agent/ — LangGraph orchestrator (week 2+)
- src/api/ — FastAPI endpoints (week 3+)

Key patterns:
- Chunks are stored with rich metadata (study_design, section, year, mesh_terms)
- Retrieval uses metadata filtering BEFORE semantic search
- Re-ranking uses Claude to score population relevance
- The agent runs multiple retrieval passes iteratively